item.title: 1.1 Sets & Numbers
item.description: Smithsonian Museum of Natural History, photo by Blake Patterson Introduction The Smithsonian in Washington, DC is one of the largest museums in the world, housing vast collections of rare and historically significant objects. The Air and Space collection, for example, holds the 1903 Wright Flyer, the first successful airplane, and the Apollo 11 Command Module from the first mission to the moon. Notable items in other collections include Abraham Lincoln’s top hat, an original Kermit the Frog puppet, and the famous Hope Diamond.

item.title: 1.1 Sets & Numbers
item.description: Section 1.1: Sets & Numbers Determine if the following sets are in set-builder notation or in roster notation. a) $\{ x ,|, x \text{ is a non-fiction book} \}$ Set-builder notation Roster notation b) $\{ \text{bass, goldfish, trout, salmon, tuna} \}$ Set-builder notation Roster notation c) $\{ x ,|, x \text{ is an animal that makes a good pet} \}$ Set-builder notation Roster notation d) $\{ 🔷, ⚪️, 🟪, 🔔, 🤎 \}$
